the default value.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Constant ","type":"text"},{"code":"MLNHillshadeMethod","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Any of the following constant string values:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"standard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": The legacy hillshade method.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"basic","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" default algorithm.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"combined","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"-combined","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"igor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"gdaldem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"-igor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" option.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"multidirectional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Hillshade with multiple illumination directions. Uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the basic hillshade model with multiple in